MORE(1)                          User Commands                         MORE(1)

NAME
       more - file perusal filter for crt viewing

SYNOPSIS
       more [options] [file ...]

DESCRIPTION
       more  is  a  filter for paging through text one screenful at a time.
       Unlike less, more can only scroll forward except in limited cases.

OPTIONS
       -d, --silent
              prompt with "[Press space to continue, 'q' to quit.]",
              display "[Press 'h' for instructions.]" instead of ringing
              the bell when an illegal key is pressed

       -l, --logical
              do not pause after any line which contains a ^L (form feed)

       -e, --exit-on-eof
              exit on end-of-file reached for the second time

       -f, --no-pause
              count logical lines, rather than screen lines

       -p, --print-over
              do not scroll; instead, clear the screen and display the
              text

       -c, --clean-print
              do not scroll; instead, paint each screen from the top,
              clearing the remainder of each line

       -s, --squeeze
              squeeze multiple blank lines into one

       -u, --plain
              suppress underlining and bold

       -n, --lines NUMBER
              specify the number of lines per screenful

       +NUMBER
              start displaying at line number NUMBER

       +/STRING
              start displaying at line containing STRING

       --help display this help and exit

       -V, --version
              output version information and exit

INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
       SPACE  display next screenful

       ENTER  display next line

       q, Q   exit more

       h, ?   display help summary

       /pattern
              search for pattern

       n      find next occurrence of pattern

       =      display current line number

       :f     display file name and current line number

       :n     skip to next file

       :p     go back to previous file

       b      go back one screenful (if input is a file)

       .      repeat previous command

       d      display next half-screenful

